      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MUSSEL SHOALS (2) looks close to another win after a very good effort last time at Shepparton, leading from wider and fighting well for second and just a nose from the winner. Has the speed to take advantage of this low draw so can go one better. CORZAN DRAMA (6) has been a model of consistency of late and deserved his success last start, scoring by 1.1 metres at this circuit and distance to follow a string of placings. Draws wider but could go right on with the job. BULLETIN (9) draws for a trail and could be close to a return to the winners' stall having come from wider barriers to place in his last two outings here. SECRETS KEPT (3) was solid from this barrier last time and did well for a 2.5m third from a wider draw here two back.",
